A three-story building in the Mushin area of Lagos State was, yesterday, destroyed by fire following an explosion of a 33,000-litre diesel laden tanker at Mobil Petrol Station, Idioro Alakara, Mushin area of Lagos State. Debris of the burnt tanker.                                 PHOTO: ADEDAMOLA SAKA  “I had to run from my working place to come here. By the time I got here, everything had been burnt down,” he said.  According to him, the Mobil Filling Station has been sealed-off by the Lagos State Safety Commission.
    
Farinloye said: “Presently, out of the 33,000 litres of  four compartments,  the explosion started while only one compartment was being discharged.
  
“With total control of the fire, the remaining three compartments are being discharged to ensure the safety of the community.”  